Parliament, Tuesday, 1 June 2021 – The Portfolio Committee on Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs will this evening have an engagement with Sarah Baartman District Municipality, Auditor General Eastern Cape; Salga; national Department of Cooperative Governance (CoGTA) and the Provincial Department of CoGTA and Treasury on the state of municipalities in the Sarah Baartman District.
	
	The municipalities are: Dr Beyers Naude, Kou-Kamma; Kouga; Sundays River Valley; Ndlambe; Makana and Blue Crane local municipalities.
	
	Details of the meeting are as follows:
	
	Date: Tuesday, 1 June 2021
	Time: 19:00-22:00
	Virtual Meeting Platform
	.
